                <h1>How to Successfully Install Wallpaper on Textured Walls</h1>
                <p>Installing wallpaper on textured walls can be challenging but rewarding. Start by cleaning the surface thoroughly to remove dust and dirt. Apply a heavy-duty wallpaper adhesive or use the paste method for better adhesion. Smooth out bubbles with a wallpaper brush, ensuring the pattern aligns properly. Consider using thicker wallpaper for better coverage on irregular surfaces to achieve a flawless finish.</p>
